    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Graves contructed from tiles forming a sloping roof over the deceased. This was a common funerary practice in classical antiquity.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
